Access\\\\\\"},{\\\\\\"text\\\\\\":\\\\\\" or another managed policy for CodeCommit access. For more information, see AWS Managed (Predefined) Policies for CodeCommit.After you have selected the policy you want to attach, choose Next: Review to review the list of policies that will be attached to the IAM user. If the list is correct, choose Add permissions.For more information about CodeCommit managed policies and sharing access to repositories with other groups and users, see Share a Repository and Authentication and Access Control for AWS CodeCommit.\\\\\\"}],\\\\\\"type\\\\\\":\\\\\\"list-item\\\\\\"}],\\\\\\"type\\\\\\":\\\\\\"numbered-list\\\\\\"}]\\"}","{\\"id\\": \\"7be1b249-63eb-4de9-86eb-ef899a8a466f\\", \\"title\\": \\"Install and configure the AWS CLI\\", \\"duration\\": 600, \\"resources\\": {\\"documentation\\": \\"\\"}, \\"description\\": \\"Description\\", \\"instructions\\": \\"[{\\\\\\"children\\\\\\":[{\\\\\\"children\\\\\\":[{\\\\\\"text\\\\\\":\\\\\\"On your local machine, download and install the AWS CLI. This is a prerequisite for interacting with CodeCommit from the command line. For more information, see Getting Set Up with the AWS Command Line Interface.\\\\\\"}],\\\\\\"type\\\\\\":\\\\\\"list-item\\\\\\"},{\\\\\\"children\\\\\\":[{\\\\\\"text\\\\\\":\\\\\\"Run this command to verify the CodeCommit commands for the AWS CLI are installed: \\\\\\"},{\\\\\\"code\\\\\\":true,\\\\\\"text\\\\\\":\\\\\\"aws codecommit help\\\\\\"},{\\\\\\"text\\\\\\":\\\\\\" This command should return a list of CodeCommit commands.\\\\\\"}],\\\\\\"type\\\\\\":\\\\\\"list-item\\\\\\"},{\\\\\\"children\\\\\\":[{\\\\\\"text\\\\\\":\\\\\\"Configure the AWS CLI with the configure command, as follows: \\\\\\"},{\\\\\\"code\\\\\\":true,\\\\\\"text\\\\\\":\\\\\\"aws configure \\\\\\"},{\\\\\\"text\\\\\\":\\\\\\"When prompted, specify the AWS access key and AWS secret access key of the IAM user to use with CodeCommit. Also, be sure to specify the AWS Region where the reposi